Congress is writing legislation to provide up to $100,000 to farmers whose crops are  wiped out by the drought, which Agriculture Secretary Richard Lyng calls the largest in  US history.
President Reagan will visit drought-stricken areas tomorrow.
UPS will ship  20-30 tons of hay daily from Oregon to Kentucky for the next two weeks, to be stored at  a fairground and sold to farmers chosen by lottery.
Farmers are angered by the delay.
Carolina and Virginia hay shipments, organized by the stock car world, will be trucked to  Ohio tomorrow.
Nevada has removed catch limits at reservoirs expected to dry up.
Rain  was widespread yesterday, and extremely heavy some places. 
